| Directory           | Command to Inspect | Description                                                             |
| ------------------- | ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `/bin â†’ /usr/bin`   | `ls -l /bin`       | Essential user commands (`ls`, `cp`, `mv`, `cat`) linked to `/usr/bin`. |
| `/sbin â†’ /usr/sbin` | `ls -l /sbin`      | System admin commands (`iptables`, `shutdown`) linked to `/usr/sbin`.   |
| `/lib â†’ /usr/lib`   | `ls -l /lib`       | Shared libraries needed by binaries, linked to `/usr/lib`.              |
# Full Linux Notes (Beginner to Advanced - DevOps Focus)

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 1. Introduction to Linux

### **What is Linux?**

Linux is an open-source operating system used to run servers, cloud platforms, DevOps tools, and production systems.

### **Why Linux for DevOps?**

* Most servers run Linux
* Kubernetes, Docker, Jenkins, Terraform all run on Linux
* SSH, networking tools, logsâ€”all Linux based
* Stability & performance

### **Where Linux is Used:**

* AWS EC2 instances
* Kubernetes nodes
* Docker containers
* CI/CD runners
* Production servers

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 2. Linux File System Structure

| Path       | Description              |
| ---------- | ------------------------ |
| `/`        | Root directory           |
| `/home`    | User directories         |
| `/etc`     | Configuration files      |
| `/var`     | Logs, cache, spool files |
| `/var/log` | System logs              |
| `/usr/bin` | User commands            |
| `/bin`     | Binary executables       |
| `/sbin`    | System binaries          |
| `/tmp`     | Temporary files          |
| `/opt`     | Optional packages        |
| `/root`    | Root user home           |

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 3. Basic Commands

### Navigation

* `pwd` â€“ Show working directory
* `ls -l` â€“ List files with details
* `cd /path` â€“ Change directory
* `cd ..` â€“ Go back one directory

### File Operations

* `touch file.txt`
* `cp file1 file2`
* `mv file1 file2`
* `rm file.txt`
* `mkdir folder`
* `cat file.txt`

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 4. Permissions & Ownership

### Permission Structure

```
drwxr-xr--  1 user group 4096 file
```

### Meaning of Symbols

* `d` = directory
* `r` = read
* `w` = write
* `x` = execute

### Changing Permissions

* `chmod 755 file`
* `chmod u+x script.sh`

### Changing Owner

* `chown user file`
* `chown user:group file`

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 5. Users & Groups

### User Commands

* `whoami`
* `id`
* `sudo su` â€“ switch to root
* `useradd username`
* `passwd username`

### Group Commands

* `groupadd devops`
* `usermod -aG devops user`

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 6. File Search Commands

### Find

* `find / -name file.txt`
* `find . -type f -size +20M`

### Grep

* `grep "error" file`
* `grep -R "503" /var/log/`

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 7. System Monitoring

### Processes

* `ps aux`
* `top`
* `htop`
* `kill PID`
* `kill -9 PID`

### Resource Usage

* `free -m`
* `df -h`
* `du -sh *`

---

## ðŸŸ¦ 8. Networking Commands

* `ip a` â€“ Show IP address
* `ping google.com` â€“ Connectivity check
* `curl http://url` â€“ Hit URL
* `ss -tulnp` â€“ Check open ports
* `hostname -I` â€“ Show IP
* `scp file user@server:/path` â€“ Copy via SSH

